  "title": "WSHO cum ECO (Construction)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Assist and advise the Project Manager in Environmental, Health, and Safety (EHS) planning for both the overall project scope and specific activities.</li>\n  <li>Review and ensure full understanding of company ISO standards, EHS requirements, and subcontract agreements.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with relevant authorities and maintain proper documentation to ensure compliance with statutory and regulatory requirements.</li>\n  <li>Conduct regular site audits to verify adherence to EHS standards, with authority to implement necessary actions, including issuing partial stop-work orders in consultation with the Project Manager.</li>\n  <li>Manage and document all accident and incident reports promptly and accurately.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate closely with the project team and subcontractors to maintain a safe and compliant working environment.</li>\n  <li>Take proactive measures to prevent fines, demerit points, or stop-work orders (SWOs) from authorities such as MOM, NEA, and HDB—this is a key responsibility and performance metric for the WSHO cum ECO role.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Preferable with Certified WSHO, ECO, ECMO</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>\n<p>EA Personnel No: R22110981</p>\n<p>EA Personnel Name: Law Mei Fong</p>",
